observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor shall:

demand from the Contractor of Salintubig Project Phase III the refund of overpayment of ₱540,816.38; 


make a written representation with DILG to follow-up the request on the release of the remaining ₱2.4 Million for Salintubig Project Phase III; 

issue a resumption order to the contractor of Salintubig Project Phase IV to complete the project, and impose liquidated damages, if necessary; and

require the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to monitor the utilization of funds transferred from different Source Agencies to avoid misapplication of funds of one project to another.

We recommend that:

The Municipal Engineer conduct an inventory of all local road projects of the Municipality and submit the corresponding report thereon, with complete description and cost segregation of road components, to the Accountant and the General Services Officer; 

The Municipal Accountant transfer to Road Network account all road projects implemented by the LGU prior to CY 2017 based on the Registry of Public Infrastructures or the Notes to Financial Statements in prior years, and;

The General Services Officer prepare a Report of Local Road Network and maintain a complete Local Road Network Property Cards for all the municipal roads and reconcile the same with the records maintained in the Accounting.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to require the Municipal Accountant:
to restore the stale checks to its respective Cash in Bank account;
to effect immediately the corresponding adjustments pertaining to valid reconciling items that remained unadjusted for over one year;
to trace and verify pervious accounting records to determine if there are erroneous recording of transactions that had caused   a negative book balance of P68,485.93 and prepare the necessary adjusting entries; and
d.  to review the bank reconciliation statement for SEF LBP – Tacloban Account No. 0182-4043-49, its subsidiary ledger, the Municipal Treasurer’s cashbook and prepare adjusting entries to correct the amount presented in the Financial Statement.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:
the Municipal Engineer to issue a Certificate of Completion on the validated completed projects to be used as basis by the Municipal Accountant in the reclassification of the CIP accounts to the proper PPE account;
the Municipal Accountant to record the projects completed in CYs 2020 and 2021 to its appropriate asset account; coordinate with the Municipal Engineer and reconcile records of prior years’ completed projects not included/booked in the PPE accounts; and take up the corresponding depreciation expenses of their classified completed projects from the time of completion until December 31, 2021, and henceforth ensure reclassification of all completed projects in the Construction in Progress account to the appropriate asset accounts.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor create an Inventory Committee that will conduct the inventory taking following the procedural guidelines provided in COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;
We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to:
to maintain a complete and up-dated Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Card and Real Property Ledger Card, so that all PPE are properly accounted for;
to prepare entries to recognize the donated equipment mentioned in paragraph numbers 4.13 and 4.14;
to derecognize items below the capitalization threshold as discussed in paragraph numbers 4.15 and 4.16;
perform periodic reconciliation between the PPELC and the Property Cards maintained by the Supply Section and ensure that discrepancies are investigated and reconciled and prepare the necessary journal entries to set the accounts in order.
We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Supply Officer to:
issue a Property Acknowledgment Receipt for donated equipment and Inventory   Custodian Slip for items below the capitalization threshold in lieu of the previously issued Property Acknowledgment Receipt;
submit to the Municipal Accountant the documents of the donated properties cited in paragraph numbers 4.13 and 4.14; and
issue Property Acknowledgment Receipt/Inventory Custodian Slip to the custodians of the said properties.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant:
stop the practice of recording inventories as outright expenses;
record the transaction following the Perpetual Inventory Method of accounting and recognize expenses based on the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued prepared and submitted by the Supply Officer;
maintain the Supplies Ledger Card for each commodity/stock as subsidiary record, and
reconcile this with the Stock Card maintained by the Supply Officer.
We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Supply Officer:
to maintain Stock Cards for each type of inventory;
issue supplies from stock based on properly filled out RIS and summarize these in the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued every month and submit this to the Municipal Accountant for recording;
to conduct regular reconciliation of the Stock Cards with the Supplies Ledger Cards maintained by the Accounting Office and to strictly follow the relevant provisions in MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor shall:

demand from the Contractor of Salintubig Project Phase III the refund of overpayment of ₱540,816.38; 


make a written representation with DILG to follow-up the request on the release of the remaining ₱2.4 Million for Salintubig Project Phase III; 

issue a resumption order to the contractor of Salintubig Project Phase IV to complete the project, and impose liquidated damages, if necessary; and

require the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to monitor the utilization of funds transferred from different Source Agencies to avoid misapplication of funds of one project to another.

We recommend that:

The Municipal Engineer conduct an inventory of all local road projects of the Municipality and submit the corresponding report thereon, with complete description and cost segregation of road components, to the Accountant and the General Services Officer; 

The Municipal Accountant transfer to Road Network account all road projects implemented by the LGU prior to CY 2017 based on the Registry of Public Infrastructures or the Notes to Financial Statements in prior years, and;

The General Services Officer prepare a Report of Local Road Network and maintain a complete Local Road Network Property Cards for all the municipal roads and reconcile the same with the records maintained in the Accounting.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor shall:

Initiate the procurement of a lot as the new dump site and develop therein a sanitary landfill as a final garbage disposal site of the LGU, upon securing permits and licenses from the DENR, in order to stop the operation of an open dump site, and;

Implement the Safe Closure and Rehabilitation Plan on the dumpsite located at Brgy. Tagharigue.
